If you have any suggestions for improving our site, please write - we will try to take everything into account and use it in the further development of the site. Author: aleksus
Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: Exchanges never use blockchain in trading. You trade with virtual numbers, only when you do deposit/withdrawal blockhain is actually used. I understand these minimum trading amounts are needed to protect against bots placing numerous orders, but it must be possible to make all-in order with reasonable sum lower than normal minimum (not fraction of cents of cause) to nullify your balance in case of exit. Programatically this check is trivial, if you place an order lower than required minimum it should be all-in order. If somebody from CObinhood team read this thread please consider this feature, I think it will be very welcomed by many of your users.

Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: Build your COBINHOOD API clients and win FREE COBs! COBINHOOD will give away 16,000 COB in total for the best examples of how to use the API. GOAL The goal is to demonstrate how to use the COBINHOOD APIs so that others can pick up your code and start to program their own algos. GAME RULES Build API clients with the following features: - Follow latest api documentation - Getting latest price of a symbol - Getting depth of a symbol or maintain a depth cache locally - Placing a LIMIT order - Placing a MARKET order - Checking an order’s status - Cancelling an order - Getting list of open orders A 2000 COB award will be given to the best submission in each of these languages: - Java - Python - Node.js - Go - C++ - C# - PHP - Objective-C Selection Criteria - Completeness of the API usage - Efficiency of algorithm - Cleanness of code - Proper logging and exception handling. - Works out of the box - Well documented, easy to understand - Any other neat features DATE Competition Starts: now Ends: whenever a suitable submission is selected for each language, or Feb 28th, 2018. HOW TO APPLY Application Email your GitHub link to code@cobinhood.com In your application, please include the following: "I,<full name> , fully own the code I submit. I guarantee there are no copyright or license restrictions. I further agree any code I submit will be in public domain. Anyone can copy, change, derive further work from it without any restrictions."

Author: semsyor
Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: Day Traders Rejoice—There’s A Free Cryptocurrency Exchange In 2018    2017 was the year of cryptocurrencies. And if you invested in them, it was probably a good year for you, as well.  While the unfathomable success of Bitcoin took the spotlight (rising from USD 1,000 to USD 20,000 over the course of the year), it wasn’t alone in its ascent. Ripple grew even more than Bitcoin did this year. Ethereum and Litecoin made monumental jumps. Even some of the altcoins made unprecedented leaps of over 15,000% in this year alone.  If you’re a swing trader, day trader, or just a general investor in any of these cryptocurrencies, your payout was probably substantial. But, you likely paid out a good amount of those profits in trade fees, as well.  Think of all that money lost to the exchange...  The problem with exchanges: high trading fees  Businesses in the financial sector tend to make a lot of money. Cryptocurrency exchanges are no different.  Coinbase, for example, charges a 1.5% fee to buy Bitcoin from their site. And its sister site, GDAX, features “taker” fees of 0.25%. So if you have $10,000 and make a single round-trip trade with all that capital (buy and sell), you’re instantly down $50. If you made 30 round-trip trades per month with all your capital? You’ve now lost $1,500, or 15% of everything you invested.  These fees, while they don’t seem high at a glance, eat away at profits. And they’re the norm everywhere. They’re why the vast majority of day traders are not profitable, even if they make decent trades. Your trades can’t just be decent if you’re making round-trip trades every day. Those fees add up quickly.  This is why Binance has become the largest exchange by daily volume in under half a year. The Shanghai-based exchange has the distinct advantage of only charging 0.10% of each trade. That’s significantly less than every other major player. Using the same $10,000 account as an example, you’d only pay out $20 per round-trip trade. These low fees, combined with Binance’s numerous trading pair offerings, has allowed it to thrive in an expensive cryptocurrency exchange ecosystem.  But 0.10% still adds up over time. And when you factor in the taxes you have to pay on your winnings, your profits dwindle all too quickly.  The truth is that trading fees are put in place to turn a profit—not to benefit customers. Most exchanges not only could care less about your bottom line, they actually factor in your “lifetime value” as a customer because they know how long someone will stay with them before they go bust.  These are all reasons why Cobinhood (COB) seems so exciting and groundbreaking. It’s the first 100% free cryptocurrency exchange. There are no fees and no commissions at all. Sound too good to be true? I did a deep dive into it to see if it lived up to the hype. Here’s what I found.  What Is Cobinhood (and why should I care)?  Cobinhood launched its exchange in December of 2017 with one goal: create a user-friendly, dependable cryptocurrency exchange with zero fees.  Taking a page out of the book of the zero-fee stock trading site Robinhood, Cobinhood’s value prop couldn’t be easier to understand. There’s no fine print or “fees that aren’t actually fees.” They are the genuine article and offer exactly what they advertise.  The wise skeptic might ask, “But how do they make money?” Good question. Rather than collecting piles of money from commissions, Cobinhood underwrites new ICOs that can be featured on their exchange. Cobinhood takes a small percentage of these new ICO coins to finance their operation. That’s how they locked in Cybermiles and helped them raise $45 million.  https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/no-really-a-free-cryptocurrency-exchange-in-2018_us_5a4e3b71e4b06cd2bd03e50a

Author: gartmah
Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: NFL superstar Richard Sherman lays out 3 issues with crypto trading  Richard Sherman is a Super Bowl winning cornerback for the Seattle Seahawks and official spokesperson for COBINHOOD, a zero-fee crypto trading platform.  This is the first season in my seven-year career where I won't get to play all 16 games. With the 2017/2018 playoffs underway, I find myself wondering what to do with all my spare time as well as who to root for since the Seahawks missed the playoffs for the first time since 2011. Like anyone, post injury, it's great to be able to spend more time with my fiancée and kids. I’m looking forward to seeing them even more frequently as I enter another rehab, focusing on removing a bone spur in my heel after my Achilles injury.  While the family time has been great, I’ve begun to work hard to stimulate myself mentally by educating myself on how blockchain and cryptocurrencies are bringing unprecedented change to the world. This world isn’t new to me, I first got involved with cryptos over five years ago and began accepting bitcoin long before people were campaigning for Amazon to allow virtual currencies as a payment method. Nevertheless, nobody could have guessed that the guy that bought two pizzas with bitcoin back in 2010 would be $100 million richer today if he had kept it…  http://www.businessinsider.com/cryptocurrencies-nfl-superstar-richard-sherman-lays-out-issues-trading-2018-1

Author: ale22
Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: THERE ARE TOO MANY COMMENTS of a concern troll accounts (EXCHANGES and other companies). It's useless to try to destroy Cobinhood, they have 0 transactions fees and better technology while other exchanges are collapsing.  It's easy to find answers to these questions, however:  - COB is a standard Ethereum ERC20 token and can be stored in Etherium address;  - The Benefits Of Being A COB token holder are:     50% off margin trading loan interest can be discounted when paid with COB tokens.  When Cobinhood underwrites an ICO, COB token holders will be able to get future ICO tokens at significantly lower rates. The amount of ICO tokens that a COB token holder can get at a lower rate is as follows:  (ICO Tokens Received by Cobinhood from ICO Underwriting Service) * (The Amount of COBs Owned) / (Total Amount of COBs)  Token holders can bind their Ethereum wallet address, which is holding COB tokens to their Cobinhood trading platform account, by calling the binding function in COB token smart contract.  After the binding is complete, COB holders can get the ICO tokens at a lower rate on the Cobinhood exchange.  As an example, Cobinhood underwrites an ICO for a token called XYZ. The total issuance of XYZ tokens through ICO is 100M and Cobinhood takes 5% as underwriter service fee. 10M COB tokens holder will have a lower rate, i.e. : 5M * 10M / 1B = 50k XYZ tokens. Cobinhood will make efforts to maximize a COB token holder’s benefits.  There may be more privileges for COB token holders in the future.  - 1 billion COB tokens was issued, half of it (500 million tokens) for ICO (they attracted more than 7,000 investors and raised $13,440,705). 400 million COBs belong to the team, while the remaining 100 million COBs will be used as private placement. Consider they invested a lot of money in technology, their systems can handle millions of transactions per second.  - There will be 9 airdrops this year. Free money. Airdrop is a coin give-away. If Cobinhood lists a new coin that is a ico, Cobinhood will be payed this for new coin listing and those free coins will be handed out to COB holders based on the number of COB. It happened recently with CMT, it was airdropped.  That's why people are buying COB, infact volume rise from 800k to 5millions, profits since ICO are huge and will continue to grow a lot.....

Body: This brilliant business concept should be quite profitable for them to fund further development, security measures, and general operational  costs. Listing fees (But, this isn't a continuous stream)  However, the funding itself is allocated in the token distribution. Author: Jim-Bo Baggins
Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: I'm also interested in this project but would like to know more about this, too. For now, it's hanging over the endeavor and giving me pause.  Additionally, I have a few other concerns. There seems to be no whitepaper or roadmap at the Cobinhood web site. Also, no explanation as to what purpose the coin serves.  Additionally, the project seems hard to contact outside of Twitter. For example, the link for "Contact Us" on the web site doesn't seem to go anywhere; same for the fly-out menu when logged in to the exchange. (Is it just me?)  I inquired about these topics with Cobinhood via Twitter DM and they person who (eventaully) responded ignored the primary questions (white paper, roadmap, coin purpose) and simply told me I was wrong and the "Contact Us" links do work. (Again, is it just me, or are others finding this as well?)  I had to prod them multiple times for answers regarding the primary questions--a brief explanation of the coin was finally provided, but regarding the white paper and roadmap they brushed it off by saying it's just not available now.  After some digging around (Google, forums) I was also able to find some information about these subjects. But it seems odd the project isn't more forthcoming about it when they easily could be right on their site. And they just seem kind of evasive when directly asked about things.  Combined with the "sketchy" report referenced above, I just get a bad vibe about this project. I want to believe in it, but they're not making it easy. It could be they are simply overwhelmed, or inexperienced or inept. But if the concern about scamming were at least put to bed, I'd feel better about it all.

Author: GlobalProtection
Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: This brilliant business concept should be quite profitable for them to fund further development, security measures, and general operational  costs.  COBINHOOD's revenue will come from margin loan interest and ICO underwriting service. It's recommended that you can check their white paper, especially CH4 and CH6: https://cobinhood.com/assets/whitepaper/whitepaper_en.pdf  And you are welcome to join their slack and telegram, lots of people discuss COBINHOOD every day.  Also, many questions are answered on URL below here:  https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2169745.msg21809115#msg21809115  Furthermore, keep these points in mind:  1. ICO underwriting - Cobinhood takes 5% or something like that. 2. Margin loans - up to 10x margin loan accumulate interest. 2.5. COB gets 50% of loaned token profit. 3. Listing fees (But, this isn't a continuous stream)  However, the funding itself is allocated in the token distribution. Whatever it says in the WP as the % to fund the development etc. However, it was said that Cobinhood didn't necessarily need the cash to launch the project, but the ICO was necessary as part of Cobinhoods' implementation.

Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: If I remember correctly, accourding to their white paper; they are using a 5/8 multisig hardware wallet that is distributed all over the world.  In simple terms, 8 people who are all in different parts of the world have a key to the safe with all the cash, at least 5 of these people are required to open the safe together in order to process a mutually agreed transaction. This means it is incredibly hard to hack, and even if a number of people were to be compromised it would still be impossibe to steal money.

Author: GlobalProtection
Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: Hello Crypto Champions:  They do not work for free and this business concept should be quite profitable for them to fund further development, security measures, and general operational  costs.  COBINHOOD's revenue will come from margin loan interest and ICO underwriting service. It's recommended that you can check their white paper, ecpecially CH4 and CH6: https://cobinhood.com/assets/whitepaper/whitepaper_en.pdf  And welcome to join their slack and telegram, lots of people discuss COBINHOOD every day.  Also, many questions answered on URL below here:  https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2169745.msg21809115#msg21809115  Also, keep these points in mind:  1. ICO underwriting - Cobinhood takes 5% or something like that. 2. Margin loans - up to 10x margin loan accumulate interest. 2.5. COB gets 50% of loaned token profit. 3. Listing fees (But, this isn't a continuous stream)  However, the funding itself is allocated in the token distribution. Whatever it says in the WP as the % to fund the development etc. However, it was said that Cobinhood didn't necessarily need the cash to launch the project, but the ICO was necessary as part of Cobinhoods' implementation.

Author: GlobalProtection
Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: Hello:  I have posted a lot of positive posts on this thread helping people and showing people why COB is an excellent choice.  BUT:  I am going to look at this from the perspective of a person who is heading up the launch of their ICO token and they are looking around to find the best place to launch their ICO token.  Would they pick Cobinhood to launch their token knowing that they will have to inflate the amount of the ICO tokens they issue in order to satisfy the people holding COB tokens who will get a massive amount of their company's ICO tokens for free?  Or, would they pick an equally good launch platform where they will not have to inflate their ICO tokens to satisfy the needs of a multitude of people who will get their company's tokens for free? Author: GlobalProtection
Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: Question given to me in post above:   yes i need to read the whitepaper but its easier to find it here cus so far 100 whitepapers gave me whitebeard, my question is what are the benefits for tokenholders? do we get any devident of the revenue came from margin loan? thnx    Hello Crypto Warrior:  I had the same question as you early on, and here is the question I asked and the answer I was given:    The question I posted: "I do want to find a compelling use-case for purchasing and holding the COB token."   Here is the answer I got before the ICO ended with less than 250 million tokens sold:    1. 50% discount on margin loan fees as opposed to paying with another currency.  2. Discounts on ICO tokens that Cobinhood underwrites; no need to swap COB for new tokens, you only need to hold them. The amount of ICO tokens that a COB holder can get at a lower rate is as follows: (ICO Tokens Received by COBINHOOD from ICO Underwriting Service) * (The Amount of COBs Owned) / (Total Amount of COBs)  3. The circulation will end at a good 250-300 million tokens after the ICO, while the rest is locked in a vesting pool to keep it that way.  4. They have also said that they will offer more privileges for token holders in the future, so thats another reason to invest if you trust in the companys ability to deliver on their promises.

Author: supersheriffen
Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: 1. 50% discount on margin loan fees as opposed to paying with another currency.  2. Discounts on ICO tokens that Cobinhood underwrites; no need to swap COB for new tokens, you only need to hold them. The amount of ICO tokens that a COB holder can get at a lower rate is as follows: (ICO Tokens Received by COBINHOOD from ICO Underwriting Service) * (The Amount of COBs Owned) / (Total Amount of COBs)  3. The circulation will end at a good 250-300 million tokens after the ICO, while the rest is locked in a vesting pool to keep it that way.  4. They have also said that they will offer more privileges for token holders in the future, so thats another reason to invest if you trust in the companys ability to deliver on their promises.

Author: potizuh
Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: Global Jobcoin, world’s first cryptocurrency for employment services, raised more than $7 Million in just a few days after announcing its presale. Powered by successful Swiss international Job Platforms Jobstoday.ch; Jobstoday.de; Jobstoday.at; Jobstoday.pl, Global Jobcoin ICO has become very popular among cryptocurrency investors & enthusiast within a few days.  It is not a surprise since Global Jobcoin ICO is backed by an established & successful company. The Job platforms are already in the market since last 3 years & have already more than 5000 clients & 1 Million + users registered on their platforms.  On the market, there are many ICOs being announced daily but most of them don’t even have any company structure, no product, no prototype or the team has no experience in product & business development. Global Jobcoin ICO has ticked all the boxes for a successful ICO. It is apparent from the presale & extremely high interest in the crowd sale. Independent ICO rating agency ICObench.com has rated Global Jobcoin 4.7 from 5.  “The fact that any investor can check that we exist since 2014 & have a working successful product in Switzerland, Germany, Austria & Poland, gives them confidence that their investment is safe with us”, said Sanket Deshmukh, Co-founder & CEO of Jobstoday & Global Jobcoin. He further added, “We receive daily at least 100 mails from our potential investors who like our ICO & are pleased to invest in it. Today’s ICO investors are smart, intelligent & they see the potential in ICOs with working product. Distribution of tokens is very important factor in deciding about the ICO. Global Jobcoin founders only hold 10% of total tokens, so the manipulation of the price is not possible. Lots of ICOs are keeping a lot of tokens for themselves so that they can manipulate the price. We have been very transparent with our investors from the beginning & that makes a big difference. Besides that, we will only have a circulating supply of 70 Million tokens & we will also invest 10% of our global profits in buying back Global Jobcoin tokens from the market.”  “Cryptocurrency investors are pushing the technology to its next level. ICOs are here to stay & the ones with successful products will give the investors a good return in short or long term”, said Lukasz Ochnik, Co-founder & CTO of Jobstoday & Global Jobcoin. He further added, “We hear about various scam ICOs daily, I personally never invested in any ICO which doesn’t have a legal company structure, experienced team & at least a prototype. Another important factor is whether the company address is revealed on the website & they can be found in company registration directory of that country. I don’t understand how people should invest in an ICO if the company does not even want to reveal its address. We spent 2 months in planning the ICO with our great team. We looked at various factors & how we can guarantee our investors the return that we promise. Our token holders not only benefit from our rising token price but also from the 20% dividends that they receive from our worldwide profits.”  The Global Jobcoin presale is currently in progress & minimum investment of 10 ETH is accepted, tokens are guaranteed through a SAFT agreement during the presale. The public crowd sale will start on October 28. The hard cap is set at 200,000 ETH, which is approximately $60 Million.  About Global Jobcoin  Global Jobcoin is an ERC20 decentralized token to pay for services related to employment. Using the Ethereum blockchain, this token is created for employers & employees worldwide. Global Jobcoin will be used on all Job platforms of Jobstoday in Switzerland, Germany, Austria & Poland. As the company expands its operations worldwide, Global Jobcoin will become the essential choice of payment on all the platforms around the world. Jobstoday is also collaborating with other partner Job boards to offer integration of Global Jobcoin into their platforms. Global Jobcoin & Jobstoday Platforms are products of Sunny Look Media LLC, registered Swiss company since 2014 in Wollerau, Canton of Schwyz.  Jobstoday Management  Sanket Deshmukh is the Co-Founder & CEO of Jobstoday & Global Jobcoin. Sanket brings 20 years of experience in Software & Business Development. Over the last 3 years, he has co-founded & built a successful multinational & multilingual recruitment platform in Switzerland Germany, Austria & Poland. His prompt, competent, & solution oriented customer skills have been received very positively by the customers.  Lukasz Ochnik is the Co-Founder & CTO of Jobstoday & Global Jobcoin. Lukasz brings over 15 years of experience in Software Development & Digital Marketing. As a co-founder & technology lead, he has always pushed the limits & implemented new innovative features on the platform. His efforts have always benefited the clients to reduce costs & save time. His ability to find perfect solutions has made him very popular among the clients.  Website: https://www.globaljobcoin.com Global Jobcoin Presale Information Start date: 22.09.2017 – 15:00 UTC Total Tokens available in Presale: 10,000,000 (10 Million) Tokens remaining for purchase in Presale: 3,000,000 (3 Million) Presale Bonus: 50-60% Bonus Token exchange rate: 1 ETH = 560 GJC (60% Bonus) Token Price: 0.53 USD Token exchange rate: 1 ETH = 525 GJC (50% Bonus) Token Price: 0.57 USD  Presale Conditions  Minimum purchase: 10 ETH (3000 USD) Maximum transaction amount: Unlimited Amount of tokens per one person: Unlimited Currencies accepted: Bitcoin (BTC), Ethereum (ETH), Ripple (XRP), Litecoin (LTC)  Tokens purchased during pre-sale will be issued during the crowd sale. Presale tokens are guaranteed with SAFT agreement.

Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: Even if you buy COB at a higher value than ICO price, you still get 50% discount on margin loan fees as opposed to paying with another currency.  The difference in privileges between holders is that if you own more COB, you can acquire more ICO tokens and margin loans at discounted rates.  The amount of ICO tokens that a COB holder can get at a lower rate is as follows: (ICO Tokens Received by COBINHOOD from ICO Underwriting Service) * (The Amount of COBs Owned) / (Total Amount of COBs)  Ripple is a payment system between banks with a circulation of 40 billion tokens.. not comparable to Cobinhood.  COB will have a circulation between 250-300 million tokens after the ICO, so the potential price gain is much higher than XRP.

Author: supersheriffen
Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: I am VERY optimistic about the potential price gain of COB.  The circulating supply will probably land at ~250 million after the ICO; unsold tokens will be vested if i understand correctly.  As a comparison we have Binance Coin, which peaked at ~3$/BNB in August with a circulation of 100 million tokens. The benefits of BNB are discounted trading fees and margin loans, but the discount percentage drops every year for 5 years. COB has discounts on both margin loans and underwritten ICO tokens with no yearly drops. There is obviously no need for a trading discount, because COBINHOOD doesnt have any trading fees!  COB is clearly a more valuable token on a more ambitious exchange platform, so when they go online in November, this coin could easily grow to at least 1$ within the first months.  My advice would be to buy cheap bags on EtherDelta right now.

Author: Dunkelson
Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: COBINHOOD FEES (from their whitepaper):  4. COBINHOOD’s Business Models  COBINHOOD will launch  4.1  Margin Trading Loan Interest Users can opt in to become margin trading loan providers and receive interest earnings with their asset deposits. COBINHOOD will automatically determine the interest rate based on margin trading loan supply and demand. A portion of earnings generated from interest payments will be collected by COBINHOOD. 4.2 COBINHOOD Prime Service for individual traders in 2018. Traders can subscribe to COBINHOOD Prime    service for higher leverage on margin trading, lower latency ticker, and higher trading API rate limit on COBINHOOD exchange. Also, COBINHOOD Prime    subscribers will have escalated customer assistance, dedicated phone support, a committed customer success account manager, and 100% uptime SLA. COBINHOOD Prime    service will be subject to annual subscription fee. 4.3 COBINHOOD High-Frequency Trading Server COBINHOOD will launch its high-frequency trading server subscription service for investment banks, hedge funds, and institutional investors. These servers will be hosted on the same network with COBINHOOD order matching engine, providing ultra low- latency ticker and unlimited API rate on the COBINHOOD exchange. Trading algorithms can be deployed onto these servers for high-frequency algorithmic trading. The high- frequency trading servers will be subject to annual subscription fee. 4.4 COBINHOOD ICO Underwriting Service A percentage of ICO tokens underwritten by COBINHOOD will be collected as underwriting service fee.  Hope that helps!

Author: letsgoman
Title: [ANN] COBINHOOD - ZERO Trading Fee Cryptocurrency Exchange
Body: Here's one of COBINHOOD's revenue comes from, ICO underwriting, we charge 5% of the new issuing tokens.  For the ICO publisher, we solve their liquidity issue, right after ICO the new issued token would be tradable in our exchange. The other exchanges are not willing to list new token, the ones accept new tokens charge unreasonable fees.  For the COB holders, COB holders would get the exclusive and super low price to buy the new issued tokens. Let's say today COBINHOOD underwrite FileCoin, COB holders can but FIL with super low price by COB.
